Algorithms and parameter sets
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GFN2-xTB — Self-contained re-implementation of the GFN2-xTB semi-empirical
  tight-binding method by Bannwarth, Ehlert, and Grimme (JCTC 2019, 15,
  1652-1671). Parametrization derived from the tblite GFN2-xTB parameter
  set (gfn2-molmom.toml). Original xTB/tblite software is licensed under
  LGPL-3.0; Druse does not link against that software but implements the
  method independently using Apple's Accelerate framework.

FASPR sidechain packing — Derived from the FASPR algorithm
  (Huang, Pearce, Zhang, Bioinformatics 2020).

Dunbrack rotamer library (dun2010bbdep.bin) — Backbone-dependent rotamer
  library by Shapovalov and Dunbrack (Structure 2011). Redistributed
  with permission; see Resources/ for any accompanying notice.

AutoDock Vina scoring function — Empirical scoring inspired by
  Trott and Olson (J. Comput. Chem. 2010, 31, 455-461).
